envMon.name: envMon
envMon.description: The AT Environment Monitoring MIB for managing and reporting data relating to voltage rails, fan speeds, temperature sensors and power supply units.

EnvMonPsbSensorType.name: EnvMonPsbSensorType
EnvMonPsbSensorType.description: Indicates the type of a Power Supply Bay Device sensor.

envMonFanTable.name: envMonFanTable
envMonFanTable.description: A table of fans installed in the device that have their fan speeds monitored by environment monitoring hardware.

envMonFanEntry.name: envMonFanEntry
envMonFanEntry.description: The description, current speed, lower threshold speed and current status of a fan.

envMonFanBoardIndex.name: envMonFanBoardIndex
envMonFanBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this fan in the board table.

envMonFanIndex.name: envMonFanIndex
envMonFanIndex.description: The numeric identifier of this fan within the context of its host board.

envMonFanDescription.name: envMonFanDescription
envMonFanDescription.description: The text description of this fan.

envMonFanCurrentSpeed.name: envMonFanCurrentSpeed
envMonFanCurrentSpeed.description: The current speed of this fan in revolutions per minute.

envMonFanLowerThreshold.name: envMonFanLowerThreshold
envMonFanLowerThreshold.description: The minimum acceptable speed of the fan (in revolutions per minute).

envMonFanAlarm.name: envMonFanAlarm
envMonFanAlarm.description: An indication of whether this fan is currently in an alarm condition. A value of TRUE indicates that its current speed is too low, FALSE indicates that the current speed is acceptable.

envMonVoltageTable.name: envMonVoltageTable
envMonVoltageTable.description: A table of voltage rails in the device that are monitored by environment monitoring hardware.

envMonVoltageEntry.name: envMonVoltageEntry
envMonVoltageEntry.description: The description, current value, upper & lower threshold settings and current status of a voltage rail.

envMonVoltageBoardIndex.name: envMonVoltageBoardIndex
envMonVoltageBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this voltage sensor in the board table.

envMonVoltageIndex.name: envMonVoltageIndex
envMonVoltageIndex.description: The numeric identifier of this voltage rail within the context of its host board.

envMonVoltageDescription.name: envMonVoltageDescription
envMonVoltageDescription.description: The text description of this voltage rail.

envMonVoltageCurrent.name: envMonVoltageCurrent
envMonVoltageCurrent.description: The current reading of this voltage rail in millivolts.

envMonVoltageUpperThreshold.name: envMonVoltageUpperThreshold
envMonVoltageUpperThreshold.description: The maximum acceptable reading of this voltage rail in millivolts.

envMonVoltageLowerThreshold.name: envMonVoltageLowerThreshold
envMonVoltageLowerThreshold.description: The minimum acceptable reading of this voltage rail in millivolts.

envMonVoltageAlarm.name: envMonVoltageAlarm
envMonVoltageAlarm.description: An indication of whether this voltage rail is currently in an alarm condition. A value of TRUE indicates that its current reading is outside its threshold range, FALSE indicates that the current reading is acceptable.

envMonTemperatureTable.name: envMonTemperatureTable
envMonTemperatureTable.description: A table of temperature sensors in the device that are monitored by environment monitoring hardware.

envMonTemperatureEntry.name: envMonTemperatureEntry
envMonTemperatureEntry.description: The description, current value, upper threshold setting and current status of a temperature sensor.

envMonTemperatureBoardIndex.name: envMonTemperatureBoardIndex
envMonTemperatureBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this temperature sensor in the board table.

envMonTemperatureIndex.name: envMonTemperatureIndex
envMonTemperatureIndex.description: The numeric identifier of this temperature sensor within the context of its host board.

envMonTemperatureDescription.name: envMonTemperatureDescription
envMonTemperatureDescription.description: The text description of this temperature sensor.

envMonTemperatureCurrent.name: envMonTemperatureCurrent
envMonTemperatureCurrent.description: The current reading of this temperature sensor in tenths of a degree Celcius.

envMonTemperatureUpperThreshold.name: envMonTemperatureUpperThreshold
envMonTemperatureUpperThreshold.description: The maximum acceptable reading of this temperature sensor in tenths of a degree Celcius.

envMonTemperatureAlarm.name: envMonTemperatureAlarm
envMonTemperatureAlarm.description: An indication of whether this temperature sensor is currently in an alarm condition. A value of TRUE indicates that its current reading is outside its threshold range, FALSE indicates that the current reading is acceptable.

envMonPsbTable.name: envMonPsbTable
envMonPsbTable.description: A table showing power supply bays in the system and info on any devices that are present.

envMonPsbEntry.name: envMonPsbEntry
envMonPsbEntry.description: The description and current status of a power supply bay device.

envMonPsbHostBoardIndex.name: envMonPsbHostBoardIndex
envMonPsbHostBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this PSB in the board table.

envMonPsbHostSlotIndex.name: envMonPsbHostSlotIndex
envMonPsbHostSlotIndex.description: The index of this PSB slot within the context of its host board. This index is fixed for each slot, on each type of board.

envMonPsbHeldBoardIndex.name: envMonPsbHeldBoardIndex
envMonPsbHeldBoardIndex.description: The index of a board installed in this power supply bay. This value corresponds to envMonPsbSensorBoardIndex for each sensor on this board. A value of 0 indicates that a board is is either not present or not supported.

envMonPsbHeldBoardId.name: envMonPsbHeldBoardId
envMonPsbHeldBoardId.description: The type of board installed in this power supply bay. The values of this object are taken from the pprXxx object IDs under the boards sub-tree in the parent MIB. A value of 0 indicates that a board is is either not present or not supported.

envMonPsbDescription.name: envMonPsbDescription
envMonPsbDescription.description: The text description of this power supply bay.

envMonPsbSensorTable.name: envMonPsbSensorTable
envMonPsbSensorTable.description: A table of environment monitoring sensors on installed power supply bay devices.

envMonPsbSensorEntry.name: envMonPsbSensorEntry
envMonPsbSensorEntry.description: The description and current status of a power supply bay device.

envMonPsbSensorBoardIndex.name: envMonPsbSensorBoardIndex
envMonPsbSensorBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this sensor in the board table.

envMonPsbSensorIndex.name: envMonPsbSensorIndex
envMonPsbSensorIndex.description: The index of this power supply bay environmental sensor, within the context of its host board.

envMonPsbSensorType.name: envMonPsbSensorType
envMonPsbSensorType.description: Indicates the type of environmental variable this sensor detects.

envMonPsbSensorDescription.name: envMonPsbSensorDescription
envMonPsbSensorDescription.description: The text description of this power supply bay environmental sensor.

envMonPsbSensorAlarm.name: envMonPsbSensorAlarm
envMonPsbSensorAlarm.description: An indication of whether this environmental sensor is currently in an alarm condition. A value of TRUE indicates that the device is in a failure condition, FALSE indicates that the device is functioning normally.

envMonFanAlarmSetEvent.name: envMonFanAlarmSetEvent
envMonFanAlarmSetEvent.description: Triggered when the monitored speed of a fan drops below its lower threshold.

envMonFanAlarmClearedEvent.name: envMonFanAlarmClearedEvent
envMonFanAlarmClearedEvent.description: Triggered when the monitored speed of a fan returns to an acceptable value, the fan having previously been in an alarm condition.

envMonVoltAlarmSetEvent.name: envMonVoltAlarmSetEvent
envMonVoltAlarmSetEvent.description: Triggered when the voltage of a monitored voltage rail, goes out of tolerance by either dropping below its lower threshold, or exceeding its upper threshold.

envMonVoltAlarmClearedEvent.name: envMonVoltAlarmClearedEvent
envMonVoltAlarmClearedEvent.description: Triggered when the voltage of a monitored voltage rail returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

envMonTempAlarmSetEvent.name: envMonTempAlarmSetEvent
envMonTempAlarmSetEvent.description: Triggered when a monitored temperature exceeds its upper threshold.

envMonTempAlarmClearedEvent.name: envMonTempAlarmClearedEvent
envMonTempAlarmClearedEvent.description: Triggered when a monitored temperature returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

envMonPsbAlarmSetEvent.name: envMonPsbAlarmSetEvent
envMonPsbAlarmSetEvent.description: Triggered when a monitored parameter of a power supply bay device goes out of tolerance.

envMonPsbAlarmClearedEvent.name: envMonPsbAlarmClearedEvent
envMonPsbAlarmClearedEvent.description: Triggered when a monitored parameter of a power supply bay device returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.
